<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2006-07-18</DATELINE><TITLE>Common Scaffolds, Diverse Recognition Profiles</TITLE><BODY>A paper in this issue of Structure reports the crystal structure of griffithsin, a lectin from red algae, and demonstrates its ability to bind and neutralize the SARS coronavirus, providing a link in understanding the evolution of lectins in this family. (Ziółkowska et al., 2006).&#3;</BODY></TEXT>